  <fr:mainmatter>
    <fr:p>Type abstraction, the phase distinction, and computational effects all play an important role in the design and implementation of ML-style module systems. We propose a simple type theoretic metalanguage <fr:strong>φML</fr:strong> for multi-phase modularity in which these concepts are treated individually, supporting the definition of high-level modular constructs such as generative and applicative functors, as well as all extant forms of structure sharing.</fr:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
